Third-party software and data dependencies
==========================================

This repository is licensed under the MIT License (see `LICENSE`). Runtime and
build dependencies are not vendored wholesale in-tree; their licenses apply
when you fetch or build them.

Rust crates
------------
Dependency licenses are constrained by `deny.toml` and recorded in `Cargo.lock`.
Run `cargo deny check` before release to confirm the current graph matches policy.

Lean 4 and Lake packages
-------------------------
The Lean project under `lean/` resolves packages listed in `lean/lake-manifest.json`
(for example Mathlib4, Batteries, aesop, and other leanprover-community packages).
Those upstream projects are primarily distributed under the Apache License 2.0
(or as stated in their respective repositories). Building the Lean layer
downloads those dependencies under their terms; this NOTICE does not replace
their license texts.

Model-generated text in benchmark artifacts
--------------------------------------------
Some committed JSON contains text produced via third-party language-model APIs.
Redistribution of that content in a public repository may be subject to provider
terms of service in addition to this project's MIT license. Track provider ToS
review in your release checklist (for example `SECURITY.md` and `CONTRIBUTING.md`
for redistribution expectations before publishing).
